owl:Ontology.dc:description: The CeCO foundation layer is intended to provide a basic layer that may even be applicable beyond eCommerce or even Commerce in general although this is not an explicit goal. The foundation layer covers these general areas 1) agreements and contracts, 2) identifiers and classifiers, 3) legal artifacts and identifiers, 4) legal entities, and 5) geo-spatial encoding.
owl:Ontology.rdfs:label: Common eCommerce Ontology (CeCO) Foundation Layer

owl:ObjectProperty.dc:description: An artifact used as proof supporting an identity claim.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Assertation Artifact

owl:ObjectProperty.dc:description: The legal identifier that is assigned to the legal entity as part of a successful identity claim.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Asserted (Legal) Identifier

owl:ObjectProperty.dc:description: The application for proof of identity that associates some legal artifact and identifier with a legal entity.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Claims Identity

owl:ObjectProperty.dc:description: Denotes a relationship between an artifact container and a contained artifact.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Contains Artifact

owl:ObjectProperty.dc:description: Denotes the relationship between a dependent artifact and the artifact upon which it depends.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Depends-Upon Artifact

owl:ObjectProperty.dc:description: Denotes that two location references describe the same referent, even if they have different spacial schemes.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Equivalent Location

owl:ObjectProperty.dc:description: Denotes that two region references describe the same referent, even if they have different spacial schemes.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Equivalent Region

owl:ObjectProperty.dc:description: Refers to a legal entity that is a member of the entity group.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Group Member

owl:ObjectProperty.dc:description: Denotes that this spacial region or location is fully enclosed within another spacial region.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Spacially Enclosed Within

owl:ObjectProperty.dc:description: Denotes that this spacial region fully encloses another spacial region or location.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Spacially Encloses

owl:ObjectProperty.dc:description: Identifies the contract to which this sub-contract belongs.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Sub Contract Of

owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: Denotes the date where the assertion made by the IdentityClaim expires.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Assertation Expiration

owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: The date where the agreement becomes effective.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Effective Date

owl:DatatypeProperty.dc:description: The date where the agreement terminates, with the exception of any surviving obligations.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Termination Date

owl:Class.dc:description: A name, designation, or denotation, that is used as a way to identify or classify an object, concept, or event, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Reference

owl:Class.dc:description: The object, concept, or event, etc. addressed by an identifier, classifier, or other reference.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Referent
